label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with solitary tumor with vascular invasion or multiple tumors, with or without vascular invasion.

label.value: Acute Myeloid Leukemia with t(16;16)(p13.1;q22); CBFB-MYH11

value.value: Acute myeloid leukemia characterized by the presence of abnormal bone marrow eosinophils and the characteristic cytogenetic abnormality t(16;16)(p13.1;q22) which results in the expression of the fusion protein CBFB-MYH11.

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pT2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with solitary tumor with vascular invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pT2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with multiple tumors, with or without vascular invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with tumor perforating the visceral peritoneum or involving the local extra hepatic structures by direct invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with periductal invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of intrahepatic bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer without regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of intrahepatic bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for intrahepatic bile duct cancer.

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Triazene Compound

value.value: Any of a class of organic compounds having an amine directly attached to an azo group. Triazene compounds act as alkylating agents and cause crosslinking of DNA.

label.value: Acute Myelomonocytic Leukemia with Abnormal Eosinophils

value.value: Acute myelomonocytic leukemia characterized by the presence of abnormal bone marrow eosinophils. It is associated with inv(16)(p13.1;q22) or t(16;16)(p13.1;q22). It has a favorable prognosis.

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of intrahepatic bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The clinical staging depends on imaging procedures.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of intrahepatic bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of gallbladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Carcinoid tumors and sarcomas are not included.  The cystic duct is now included in this classification scheme. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of gallbladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The pathologic staging is based on examination of the surgical resection specimen. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of gallbladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gallbladder cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of gallbladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gallbladder cancer with metastases to nodes along the cystic duct, common bile duct, hepatic artery, and/or portal vein. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gallbladder cancer with metastases to periaortic, pericaval, superior mesenteric artery, and/or celiac artery lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of gallbladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for gallbladder cancer.

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of gallbladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The clinical evaluation usually depends on the results of ultrasonography, computed tomography, and magnetic resonance cholangiopancreatography.  Clinical staging may also be based on findings from surgical exploration (laparoscopic or open) when the main tumor mass is not resected.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of gallbladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gallbladder cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gallbladder cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage I Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage I includes: T1, N0, M0. T1: Tumor invades lamina propria or muscular layer.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage II Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage II includes: T2, N0, M0.  T2: Tumor invades perimuscular connective tissue; no extension beyond serosa or into liver.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage III Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage III includes: IIIA (T3, N0, M0); IIIB (T1-3, N1, M0). T3: Tumor perforates the serosa (visceral peritoneum) and/or directly invades the liver and/or one other adjacent organ or structure, such as the stomach, duodenum, colon, pancreas, omentum, or extrahepatic bile ducts.  T1: Tumor invades lamina propria or muscular layer.  T2: Tumor invades perimuscular connective tissue; no extension beyond serosa or into liver. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  N1: Metastases to nodes along the cystic duct, common bile duct, hepatic artery, and/or portal vein.  M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA (T4, N0-1, M0); IVB (Any T, N2, M0); (Any T, Any N, M1).  T4: Tumor invades the main portal vein or hepatic artery, or invades two or more extrahepatic organs or structures.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  N1: Metastases to nodes along the cystic duct, common bile duct, hepatic artery, and/or portal vein. N2: Metastases to periaortic, pericaval, superior mesenteric artery, and/or celiac artery lymph nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis.  M1: Distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Childhood Astrocytic Tumor

value.value: An astrocytic tumor appearing before the age of twenty one without designation of benign or malignant nor designated location.

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of perihilar bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Sarcomas and carcinoid tumors are not included. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of perihilar bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The pathologic staging is based on examination of the resected specimen and/or biopsies sufficient to document the greatest extent of the disease. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of perihilar bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer with tumor confined to the bile duct, with extension up to the muscle layer or fibrous tissue. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer with tumor invading beyond the wall of the bile duct to surrounding adipose tissue or tumor invading adjacent hepatic parenchyma. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pT2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer with tumor invading beyond the wall of the bile duct to surrounding adipose tissue. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pT2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer with tumor invading adjacent hepatic parenchyma. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Sarcoma by FNCLCC Grade

value.value: Grading of sarcomas according to the French Federation of Cancer Centers Sarcoma Group (FNCLCC). This sarcoma grading system is based on three factors: differentiation, mitotic count, and tumor necrosis. The scores for each factor are added to determine the grade (1 to 3) for the sarcoma.

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer with tumor invading unilateral branches of the portal vein or hepatic artery. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer with tumor invading the main portal vein or its branches bilaterally; or the common hepatic artery; or the second-order biliary radicals bilaterally; or unilateral second-order biliary radicals with contralateral portal vein or hepatic artery involvement. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of perihilar bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Perihilar Bile Duct Cancer pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Perihilar bile duct cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
